&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust Doctors (CT1/2 or ST1/2 level equivalent) – Acute &amp; Acute and General Medicine &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are currently excellent opportunities at Torbay and South Devon NHS Foundation Trust for doctors wishing to enhance their CV, prior to either Core Training or Specialty Training applications. These posts are to enhance the overall medical workforce and to provide flexible support (in-hours) to medical wards and also to the Emergency Assessment Units &amp; MRU.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dynamic, enthusiastic and motivated doctors to join our clinical teams in Acute and general internal medicine to include.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are opportunities to undertake a diverse range of clinical work and these posts will be invaluable for those looking to gain more medical experience prior to undertaking their next training post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All post will have on-call commitments at CT level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post(s) are available from October 2020 to end of March 2021 (6 months) and are based at Torbay Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As one of the first organisations in the country to bring together the provision of acute and community health and social care, we are the ideal place to test fresh ideas and to be part of real change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust has a great reputation for education and training, supported by feedback from Health Education England, working across the South West. We are leaders in innovation and have been at the forefront of many national service improvement initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basic salary will be £38,694 per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Alice Miller, Acute Lead, - alice.miller1@nhs.net 01803 654275&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lesley Wade, System Manager Acute Care, - lesley.wade@nhs.net 01803 656296&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deborah Honeywill, Operational Support Manager, deborah.honeywill@nhs.net 01803 655414&lt;/p&gt;
